# Partial-locale docs (cross-repo)

- Public doc URLs for partial locales must use **one** path prefix: `/verifik-{locale}/<category>/<page>/`. Never store or suggest `/verifik-fr/fr-docs/...` or other `*-docs` segments.
- Process and country rollout checklist: see **`docs/PARTIAL_LOCALE_DOCS.md`** in this repo (points to `verifik-documentation/internal/PARTIAL_LOCALE_DOCS_PLAYBOOK.md`).
- After MDX changes in the docs repo, run **`verifik-backend/scripts/seed-app-feature-docs.js`** to refresh `AppFeature.docs` (use `--dry-run` and `--only=` when scoping).
